parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to blown head gaskets, melted spark plugs, and water pump failure, which can result in costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the brake rotors can cause reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the transmission/engine control module can cause the engine to die when downshifting, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The wind noise and seal issues can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
The acceleration issues can cause reduced vehicle performance, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: hesitation when pressing the gas pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic speedometer sensor can cause the vehicle to seize or lose speed control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: the vehicle seizes or loses speed control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction during sudden stops, increasing the risk of injury or accident.
symptoms: The front seat belt will not retract
the seat belt can go into the windshield during sudden stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift gear can cause the vehicle to jerk violently or lose gear control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The shift gear will not move
the vehicle jerks violently when shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle speed control valve can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at low speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while idling
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating from a stop
the "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at low speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle surges forward without input from the driver
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels stuck
the vehicle is difficult to control or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become stuck, making it impossible to use, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt gets stuck in the holder and will not release
the seatbelt performs erratically when the seat is moved forward
